				<li id="16794430" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1667785846000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580292/Ancient-Dragons'-Lightning-Strike" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">06 Nov 2022 20:50</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16794430" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This incantation causes six bolts of roughly evenly-spaced lightning bolts to strike several times in all directions away from you. Despite what the bolts may suggest, they only harm targets that intersect with the bolts&apos; points of impact on the ground.This quirk means that beasties with have narrow feet and huge bodies suspended above the ground can miraculously escape damage without making any apparent sense.<br/>Dragons and Ancient Dragons are especially notorious for escaping the wrath of this incantation, often completely unscathed.<br/><br/>When using this, take time to memorize its exact pattern, and then position and angle yourself accordingly for maximum devastation.<br/>— Courh the Explorer</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16794430" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16794430" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section clas