				<li id="16605580" class="cmnt-root" data="47" data-d="1649412514000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580292/Ancient-Dragons'-Lightning-Strike" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Apr 2022 06:08</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16605580" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I have never put any comments online in my entire life, but I think this is too exciting for people who are really struggling to find a good lightning build for PVP. I have tried many builds to make flashy ancient lightning incantations viable in duels—from making poise monster with lightning, pairing lightning with endure, pairing lightning with 70 virtual dex, and so on (oh and for those that are confused if dex increases ancient dragoncult casting speed or not: they do. It&apos;s just that when you activate the incantations, they have two animations. The first animation when dragoncult symbol pops up is the casting animation that you can speed up with dex, the flashy animation that comes after it is the long wind up animation that you cannot speed up with anything. Amir made a video about casting speed on youtube). Sadly I could not find the builds that can compete with meta builds. The only one that I think has killing potential with 70 dex short wind up casting speed is death lightning that can deal more than 2k damage... or deal nothing at all because of the RNG hitbox. Basically it&apos;s a lightning russian roulette. Scott Jund made a showcase of it on youtube.<br/><br/>That is until I found out the strength of ancient dragons&apos; lightning strike. While your enemy is in the distance, sure this incantation has not so consistent hitbox that can sometimes hit people rolling away. 4/10 consistency. But when you bait people to trade with you up close using this and pairing it with the ash of war Endure... I cannot believe that the lightning strike can hit your enemies multiple times. With 50 faith and gravel stone, 1 strike deals around 700-800, 2 strikes deal 1400-1500, 3 STRIKES (yes the lightning strike can hit your enemies three times. Either that or three of the lightning strikes hitbox can hit your enemies at the same time) can deal 2000-2100 damage. In my experience, this has 8/10 consistency, and this is coming from a person that keeps dueling all day with the same build. The only time people can dodge this is only if they decide not to trade with me when they see you activate endure. Even then, if they roll out in or to the direction of the scattering lightning strike, it can still strike them for 700 damage. This setup even applies to people using Bloodhound Step, the ash of war that Dark Souls veterans like Jeenine and Scott kept saying is broken because of its infinite i-frames that removes any skillcap.<br/><br/>So for all lightning lovers out there, this is your trump card. After you deal heavy damage to your opponent, the rest is for you to decide on how to finish the job, considering if they are not dead yet after tanking the lightning strikes. Hope you guys can find better lightning builds and hope for lightning incantations to get buffed in the future.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16605580" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16605580" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>48</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16605580"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16605580" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16605580"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
