				<li id="16596112" class="cmnt-root" data="-8" data-d="1649218431000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580292/Ancient-Dragons'-Lightning-Strike" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">06 Apr 2022 00:13</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16596112" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">All the dragon cult incantations are garbage, but this one is slightly less garbage than the rest.  Cast time is barely usable (far better than the hilariously bad cult&apos;s usual cast times), and the sheer quantity of bolt means that bosses with large hitboxes take disproportionately damage.  On the downside, you&apos;re relying on RNG hoping a lot of bolts land on the boss.  Additionally, most normal human-sized enemies will straight up not get hit by bolts about half the time and get free hits on you; making this an unexpectedly crappy spell for crowds.  It&apos;s just barely worth the slot it takes up.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16596112" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16596112" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span>